CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 19, 1955, pg. 21 reads: "Star Time - Sports celebrities were very much in evidence at the William Penn Hotel Sunday night at the annual Dapper Dan sports banquet... The other picture provides proof that the baseball season isn't far off. Diamond stars shown are, left to right, Bob Turley, New York Yankees; Larry Doby, Cleveland; Frank Thomas and Curt Roberts, Pirates.  Ford has been signed by the Cleveland Browns.-Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of baseball players from left: Bob Turley of New York Yankees, Larry Doby of Cleveland Indians, and Frank Thomas and Curt Roberts of Pittsburgh Pirates, standing in William Penn Hotel for Dapper Dan banquet
